<caption id="DF736679A84BFFCC0CBA1480FC269488" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3587227" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3587227" box="[151,967,1732,1757]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3587227/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" startId="40.[151,250,1732,1757]" targetBox="[174,1413,211,1635]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84BFFCC0CBA1480FC269488" blockId="40.[151,967,1732,1757]" box="[151,967,1732,1757]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B978EAE3A84BFFCC0CBA1480FEC19488" bold="true" box="[151,288,1732,1757]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">FIGURE 22.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D72A84BFFCC0D0B1480FE159489" authority="Perkins, 2019" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2019" box="[294,500,1732,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hellmani" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B978EAE3A84BFFCC0D0B1480FE159489" box="[294,500,1732,1756]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Hydrochus hellmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24B5798A84BFFCC0DD71481FDD39489" box="[506,562,1733,1756]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, habitus and male genitalia of holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84BFFCC0CEA154EFC0E95C4" blockId="40.[151,1437,1802,2045]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B978EAE3A84BFFCC0CEA154EFE379570" bold="true" box="[199,470,1802,1829]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Differential Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Among Venezuelan species, recognized by the combination of small size (ca. 
<quantity id="4CF49B14A84BFFCC0946154FFF26951C" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.37" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.37">2.37 mm</quantity>
), the pronotum with moderately deep impressions separated by narrow reliefs, the elytra with large and deep strial punctures, interstriae and spaces between punctures narrow ridges, and the male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13372A74A84BFFCC08FC1517FAC49538" box="[1233,1317,1875,1901]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,211,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[151,1435,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 22. Hydrochus hellmani n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3587227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3587227/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
; described below). Completely reliable determinations will include dissection of males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C316657AA84BFFCD0CEA15DEFCA8909A" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84BFFCD0CEA15DEFEDB92AE" blockId="40.[151,1437,1802,2045]" lastBlockId="41.[151,1437,153,755]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B978EAE3A84BFFCC0CEA15DEFEB095E0" bold="true" box="[199,337,1946,1973]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Description</emphasis>
. Habitus as illustrated (
<figureCitation id="13372A74A84BFFCC0E4D15DFFD5795E0" box="[608,694,1947,1973]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,211,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[151,1435,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 22. Hydrochus hellmani n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3587227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3587227/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Size: 
<typeStatus id="54B78853A84BFFCC0F2615DFFC8C95E0" box="[779,877,1947,1973]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">holotype</typeStatus>
male (length/width, mm): body (length to elytral apices) 2.37/0.92; head width 0.60; pronotum l/w 0.53/0.57; PA 0.55; PB 0.47; elytra 1.50/0.92. Body size small (ca. 
<quantity id="4CF49B14A84BFFCC0CE515A7FED095A8" box="[200,305,2019,2045]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.37" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.37">2.37 mm</quantity>
). Dorsum black, with slight iridescence, elytra without black spots. Legs dark brown. Punctation on elytra large, deep, ca. 2– 
<date id="FFB21031A84AFFCD0D8512DDFE2392E6" box="[424,450,153,179]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">3x</date>
that of pronotum. Elytra interstriae much narrower than strial puncture diameter, narrow ridges. Interstria 9 
<superScript id="7C799BB9A84AFFCD0D4A12F8FE95929F" attach="left" box="[359,372,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">th</superScript>
more convex than others, weakly overhanging 10 
<superScript id="7C799BB9A84AFFCD0F8212F8FC5D929F" attach="left" box="[943,956,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">th</superScript>
interstria. Usual area of callus on 5 
<superScript id="7C799BB9A84AFFCD097812F8FA83929F" attach="left" box="[1365,1378,188,202]" fontSize="6" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">th</superScript>
very weakly raised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84AFFCD0CEA1341FAE29316" blockId="41.[151,1437,153,755]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Pronotum slightly wider than long (as ca. 53/57), widest at anterior margin, narrowed at base, sides very weakly arcuate, smooth; anterior margin very weakly bisinuate; depressions moderately deep, reliefs narrow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84AFFCD0CEA1309FCF293DE" blockId="41.[151,1437,153,755]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Elytra with spaces between strial punctures narrow ridges; apices rather sharply conjointly rounded in dorsal view, in lateral view outer margin with slight angulation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84AFFCD0CEA13D1FD629386" blockId="41.[151,1437,153,755]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Ventral characters: Mentum moderately coarsely and moderately densely punctate, with shallow median fovea. Submentum with two small shallow foveae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84AFFCD0CEA1399FC9C90D2" blockId="41.[151,1437,153,755]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13372A74A84AFFCD0D561399FE2F93A2" box="[379,462,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,211,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[151,1435,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 22. Hydrochus hellmani n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3587227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3587227/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) general characters: genitalia stout; paramere tips tapering and arcing slightly toward midline, extending slightly beyond distal end of aedeagus, parameres in lateral view arcuate, and wider than dorsal/ ventral views; basal piece much shorter than parameres, tapering from distal end to base, orifice sclerotized, asymmetrical; aedeagus lanceolate, lateral margins moderately widely sclerotized, greatest width at about midlength, tapering apically, with internal lumen in basal ½, gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84AFFCD0CEA10D5FA6F90FE" blockId="41.[151,1437,153,755]" box="[199,1422,657,683]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Dorsal surface: adtl subapical; pdmm widely overlapping alm, especially in distal 1/2; adbl moderately large.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84AFFCD0CEA10F1FCA8909A" blockId="41.[151,1437,153,755]" box="[199,841,693,719]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Ventral surface: avtl subbasal; pvmm approximating alm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C316657AA84AFFCD0CEA109DFB7390A6" box="[199,1170,729,755]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB336F1A84AFFCD0CEA109DFB7390A6" blockId="41.[151,1437,153,755]" box="[199,1170,729,755]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B978EAE3A84AFFCD0CEA109DFEAF90A6" bold="true" box="[199,334,729,755]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for John Leroy Hellman, who collected the only known specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
